=== 数字版权管理 ===
EPUB文件可以随意的作为附加层包含[[数字版权管理|数字版权管理]]，但这不是规范所要求的。<ref name="idpf_faq">{{cite web |url=http://www.idpf.org/forums/viewtopic.php?t=22 |title=IDPF's Digital Book Standards FAQs |author=IDPF |date=November 20, 2006 |work=IDPF |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090903065251/http://www.idpf.org/forums/viewtopic.php?t=22 |archivedate=2009年9月3日 |accessdate=2013年3月18日 }}</ref>另外，规范没有指定任何特定的数字版权管理系统，所以出版商可以自由地选择适合的数字版权管理计划。然而，未来版本的EPUB（即OCF）''可能会''指定数字版权管理的格式。<ref name="ocf2.0.1_spec"/>

EPUB规范没有强制或推荐使用特定的[[数字版权管理|数字版权管理]]计划。这可能会影响[[电子书阅读器|设备]]对不同数字版权管理系统所支持的水平以及购买电子书的便捷性。因此，这些数字版权管理的不兼容可能会按照数字版权管理系统分裂EPUB格式，这将破坏单一标准格式的优势，使得消费者迷惑。<ref name="ftimes_epub_drm1">{{cite web |url=http://www.ft.com/cms/s/0/a00ad6f8-0d0b-11df-a2dc-00144feabdc0.html |title=Walls close in on e-book garden |author=Gelles, David |date=January 29, 2010 |work=Financial Times |accessdate=2013-03-18 |archive-date=2013-11-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131113072923/http://www.ft.com/cms/s/0/a00ad6f8-0d0b-11df-a2dc-00144feabdc0.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="teleread_epub_drm1">{{cite web |url=http://www.teleread.org/2009/08/13/adobe-drmed-epub-isnt-an-open-standard-will-nyt-distinguish-between-nonproprietary-and-common/ |title=Adobe-DRMed ePub isn’t  ‘open’: Why the New York Times urgently needs to clarify its Sony eBook Store article |author=Rothman, David |date=August 13, 2009 |work=TeleRead: Bring the E-Books Home |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091014155708/http://www.teleread.org/2009/08/13/adobe-drmed-epub-isnt-an-open-standard-will-nyt-distinguish-between-nonproprietary-and-common/ |archivedate=2009年10月14日 |accessdate=2013年3月18日 }}</ref><ref name="teleread_epub_drm2">{{cite web |url=http://www.teleread.org/2009/12/21/does-the-nook-use-its-own-incompatible-drm-scheme/ |title=Does the Nook use its own incompatible DRM scheme? |author=Biba, Paul |date=December 21, 2009 |work=TeleRead: Bring the E-Books Home |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091228095050/http://www.teleread.org/2009/12/21/does-the-nook-use-its-own-incompatible-drm-scheme/ |archivedate=2009年12月28日 |accessdate=2013年3月18日 }}</ref><ref name="teleread_epub_drm3">{{cite web |url=http://www.teleread.org/2010/01/28/ipad-adds-to-the-drm-mess-apple-ebook-drm-exclusive-to-apple-hardware/ |title=iPad adds to the DRM mess?  Apple ebook DRM exclusive to Apple hardware |author=Biba, Paul |date=January 28, 2010 |work=TeleRead: Bring the E-Books Home |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100202222003/http://www.teleread.org/2010/01/28/ipad-adds-to-the-drm-mess-apple-ebook-drm-exclusive-to-apple-hardware/ |archivedate=2010年2月2日 |accessdate=2013年3月18日 }}</ref><ref name="jkontherun_epub_drm1">{{cite web |url=http://jkontherun.com/2010/01/28/who-really-needs-an-ipad/ |title=Who Really Needs an iPad? |author=Kendrick, James |date=January 28, 2010 |work=jkOnTheRun |access-date=2013-03-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100805030337/http://jkontherun.com/2010/01/28/who-really-needs-an-ipad/ |archive-date=2010-08-05 |dead-url=yes }}</ref><ref name="adobe_epub_drm1">{{cite web |url=http://blogs.adobe.com/digitaleditions/2010/01/epub_ipad_and_content_interope.html |title=EPUB, iPad and Content Interoperability |author=Dave Dickson |date=January 27, 2010 |work=Digital Editions |accessdate=2013-03-18 |archive-date=2013-02-20 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130220220156/http://blogs.adobe.com/digitaleditions/2010/01/epub_ipad_and_content_interope.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>

